ShareOverviewSummaryPacific Gas And Electric Co. has worked on twenty-six contracts worth $11.9 million USD in obligations from the federal government since FY2007. In its latest active fiscal year (2013), the organization received a total of $162,354 USD in obligations.The principal agencies it has contracted with are the Department of Defense, Department of the Treasury, and Social Security Administration.

